A class as simple as:

public static void main(String[] args) {
new JFrame.show();
}

is sufficient to expose the issue.

Right click on the Class with a Main method, select "Profile As..."
Do "Profile"
Ensure "Basic Memory Analysis" is selected in the "Monitor" Tab
Let the system switch to the "Profiling and Logging" perspective
After the JFrame appears, double click on the "Basic Memory Analysis" to trigger the Dialog and Error.
